my suggestion was to memorize the function in your package, not in the example. Examples are not run independently, but collated into a single file (EWCR-Ex.R in the EWCR.Rcheck directory, after running R CMD check) and sourced. And the suggestion was not to solve the problem of examples running slowly, but avoiding repeatedly calculating the same value. For instance, from Herv??s email ewceData::tt_alzh could be memorized in the package. The first call would take several seconds, but subsequent calls would be instantaneous. But as Herv? says that function should be cleaned up anyway so that 'tricks' like memorization might not be necessary.


