Hi,

Yes, you may retain your ability to push upstream (git.bioconductor.org) as well. The only requirement is only ONE maintainer is listed on the Package DESCRIPTION file, usually the one who takes full responsibility for the maintenance.

There is no concept of co-maintainers, only co-authors. But multiple authors can have push access if requested.

Best,

Nitesh


